---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
import AboutHeroImage from '../assets/blog-placeholder-about.jpg';
---

<Layout
	title="About Me"
	description="Learn more about Devon Garbalosa, software developer and tech enthusiast"
	pubDate={new Date('July 12 2025')}
	heroImage={AboutHeroImage}
>
	<p>
		Hi! I'm Devon Garbalosa, a passionate software developer with a love for creating innovative solutions
		and exploring the ever-evolving world of technology. Welcome to my corner of the internet where
		I share my thoughts, experiences, and learnings from my journey in tech.
	</p>

	<h2>My Background</h2>
	<p>
		I'm a developer who believes in the power of clean code, continuous learning, and collaborative
		problem-solving. My experience spans various technologies and frameworks, and I'm always eager
		to dive into new challenges and expand my skill set.
	</p>

	<h2>What I Do</h2>
	<p>
		I specialize in modern web development, with a focus on creating scalable, performant applications.
		I enjoy working with cutting-edge technologies and frameworks, and I'm particularly interested in:
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Full-stack web development</li>
		<li>Modern JavaScript frameworks and libraries</li>
		<li>Cloud computing and serverless architectures</li>
		<li>Developer tools and productivity</li>
		<li>Open source contributions</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Why I Write</h2>
	<p>
		This blog serves as a platform for me to document my learning journey, share insights I've gained,
		and contribute to the developer community. I believe that teaching others is one of the best ways
		to solidify your own understanding, and I hope my content helps fellow developers on their journeys.
	</p>

	<h2>Let's Connect</h2>
	<p>
		I'm always interested in connecting with fellow developers, learning from others' experiences,
		and collaborating on interesting projects. Feel free to reach out if you'd like to discuss
		technology, share ideas, or just say hello!
	</p>

	<p>
		<strong>Currently:</strong> Building awesome things with modern web technologies and sharing
		the journey along the way.
	</p>
</Layout>
